6 § 4468b. MAXIMUM INCREASE IN RENT
7 (a) A landlord shall not increase rent during any 12-month period in an
8 amount greater than three percent plus the Consumer Price Index above the
9 existing rent, as published by the Bureau of Labor Statistics of the United
10 States Department of Labor in September of the prior calendar year, or eight
11 percent, whichever is lower.
12 (b) A landlord shall specify in a notice of increase of rent:
13 (1) the amount of the rent increase;
14 (2) the amount of the new rent; and
15 (3) the date on which the increase becomes effective.
16 (c) A landlord shall notify a tenant of an increase in rent not less than 90
17 days prior to the date the increase takes effect.
18 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
19 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
